About Couchdb {{{1

CouchDB is a "document-oriented database".

Instead of regimented tables and rows, in CouchDB you store "documents", where each document is a set of
key/value pairs. Think of this like a Python dictionary, or a JSON document.

Stores document versions

Interface is HTTP so any programming language can connect

Replication is built-in

CouchDB also comes with an in-built in-browser editor, so you can look at and
browse around and edit all the data stored in it.

Major effort by Ubuntu to use couchdb as common application data backend.  Local couch synchronizes with Ubuntu One cloud.

Desktop Couch {{{1

Do not need to start manually
desktopcouch-pair program in the desktopcouch-tools package: synchronize if not using Ubuntu One

Starting with 
http://freedesktop.org/wiki/Specifications/desktopcouch/Documentation/SimpleGuide

1. Enter keygring password
2. Needs to read /etc/couchdb


